The paper deals with designing a lightweight and robust portrait segmentation algorithm, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new architecture based on concentrated-comprehensive convolutions block, which involves deep learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on a public dataset (EG1800), which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper analyzes the bias in public datasets, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
